This paper deals with the construction of network-error correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of finite fields, which is a common tool in network coding (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and computational methods (cs.SI), as well as the design and analysis of codes (cs.DS) and the study of communication networks (cs.CC).
